<p>Asp.Net 4.5 (WebForms)</p>  <p>How can I exclude the container div from async postback? The container is rendering webgl. I tried adding it to the Triggers as suggested on other searches but I get an error.</p>  <p><strong>Error</strong></p>  <ul> <li>Control with ID 'container' being registered through RegisterAsyncPostBackControl...</li> </ul>  <p><strong>Note</strong></p>  <ul> <li>If I move the container outside of the updatepanel then it works, however the location would be wrong then.</li> </ul>  <p><strong>Example</strong></p>  <pre><code> &lt;div id="main" class="main"&gt;         &lt;asp:UpdatePanel ID="UpdatePanel1" runat="server" UpdateMode="Conditional"&gt;             &lt;ContentTemplate&gt;                  &lt;div&gt;                     &lt;div&gt;                        more controls ...                     &lt;/div&gt;                 &lt;/div&gt;                  &lt;div id="container" class="container" runat="server"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;                  &lt;div&gt;                         more controls ...                 &lt;/div&gt;                &lt;/ContentTemplate&gt;            &lt;Triggers&gt;                &lt;asp:PostBackTrigger ControlID="container" /&gt;            &lt;/Triggers&gt;         &lt;/asp:UpdatePanel&gt;     &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>